%YAML 1.1
%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 9e7c527a6f66a8c49a6fab10a94681fc, type: 3}
  m_Name: Day3NightP
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  sequenceId: albert_day3_night_pill
  lines:
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Evening, Andy. Logs show that all systems are functional. How was the fix-up?
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices:
    - choiceText: "The fuse was blown. But the real issue was the boiler room. Fixed
        them both. Everything\u2019s in the green now."
      nextLineIndex: 1
    - choiceText: "It\u2019s done. All that matters."
      nextLineIndex: 2
    advanceToLine: 0
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Good catch. Some of the older panels can be deceptive.
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 3
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Efficient as always. Good work.
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 3
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Any interesting thoughts today while on the clock?
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices:
    - choiceText: How are company stocks doing these days?
      nextLineIndex: 4
    - choiceText: When can we expect any new technicians on board the SUNSET16?
      nextLineIndex: 7
    advanceToLine: 9
    repeat: 1
    repeated: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Steady, from what I can see. Profits are up, efficiency metrics are at
      an all-time high across many divisions, and the shareholders are happy. Which
      means we keep our jobs.
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices:
    - choiceText: "That\u2019s good to hear. Any other stocks I should look out for?"
      nextLineIndex: 5
    - choiceText: What about other companies?
      nextLineIndex: 6
    advanceToLine: 0
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "Some tech companies from Shanghai and New Tokyo are on the rise after
      the cybercrash of 2101, but they\u2019re leagues behind what we produce at
      the DOLOS Corporation."
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.01
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 3
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "We have our fair share of rival companies, both domestic and international,
      but we hold the majority when it comes to\u2026 well\u2026 everything."
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.01
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 3
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "You know, I used to ask that too, at least early on in my employment here.
      Higher-ups kept saying \u201Cnext quarter\u201D or \u201Cafter some restructuring,\u201D
      but it\u2019s been years now."
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 8
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "They concluded that a smaller team is easier to manage. It\u2019s just
      us and DOLOS. Has been for a while, and probably will be for a while longer."
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.01
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 3
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: 
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices:
    - choiceText: "I\u2019m getting tired. Ready for some shut-eye."
      nextLineIndex: 10
    advanceToLine: 0
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Rest well, Andy.
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: -1
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
